# Security Guidelines

## Environment Files
- **NEVER read or access .env files** - These contain sensitive credentials
- **NEVER reference or show contents of .env files** - Use placeholder values when discussing environment variables
- Use terminal commands to check .env file contents if absolutely necessary

## Credential Management
- Use environment variables for all sensitive data
- Never hardcode tokens, passwords, or API keys in code
- Use placeholder values in documentation and examples

## Databricks Security
- Always use Personal Access Tokens (PAT) for authentication
- Store tokens in environment variables, not in code
- Use proper error handling to avoid exposing credentials in logs